A Limit Order Book (LOB) is the heart of most trading systems (like stock exchanges).

Limit Order
    Buy or sell at a specific price
    Example:
        Buy 100 shares at ₹50 → only execute at 50 or better

Order Book Structure

    Two sides:

    BUY SIDE (Bids)        SELL SIDE (Asks)
    -----------------      -----------------
    Price: 50 Qty: 100     Price: 52 Qty: 200
    Price: 49 Qty: 150     Price: 53 Qty: 300

    Buy     → highest price first
    Sell    → lowest price first

Core C++ Concepts
    STL (priority_queue)
    Custom comparators
    Value semantics
    Struct design